        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD refers to J. T. Gulick 1872a.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">For Frans Cornelis Donders’ proposed visit to Down on either 30 or 31 July, see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8425.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from William Bowman, 24 July 1872</ref>. In the event, Gulick visited CD on 2 August (<ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin’s</ref> diary (DAR 242)). CD was so interested in their conversation that he invited Gulick to stay for dinner in order to continue the discussion (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_3191.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">A. Gulick 1932</ref>, p. 234).</note>
